member.remarks:
             Provides a standard  implementation which raises the  event.


             
             Note to implementors: this must be called each time a property-specific or action-specific event is published,
             passing the name of the event and its EventArgs as parameters.


             
             To implement a standard  on a subclass of
             :
             
             
             public class MyElement : DOMObject
             {
                 public event PropertyChangedEventHandler<int> MyPropertyChanged;
            
                 public int MyProperty
                 {
                     get
                     {
                         if (IsDisposed)
                             throw new ObjectDisposedException(null);
            
                         return myProperty.Value;
                     }
                     set
                     {
                         if (value != MyProperty)
                             myProperty.Value = value;
                     }
                 }
            
                 private UndoableProperty<int> myProperty = new UndoableProperty<int>();
            
                 public MyElement() : base()
                 {
                     myProperty.ValueChanged += delegate(object sender, PropertyChangedEventArgs<int> e)
                     {
                         if (IsDisposed)
                             throw new ObjectDisposedException(null);
            
                         if (IsFrozen)
                             throw new ObjectFrozenException();
            
                         // first send the property-specific event
                         if (MyPropertyChanged != null)
                             MyPropertyChanged(this, e);
            
                         // then send the generic event, passing the name of the property-specific event
                         // and its EventArgs
                         OnChanged(this, "MyPropertyChanged", e);
                     };
                 }
             }

member.example:
If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 NEW_MATERIAL PARAM1 PARAM2 then  should
be constructed as follows:

UnknownMaterial material = new UnknownMaterial("NEW_MATERIAL PARAM1 PARAM2");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 then  should
be constructed as follows:

PlasticMaterial material = new PlasticMaterial("");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 CHROME then  should
be constructed as follows:

ChromeMaterial material = new ChromeMaterial("CHROME");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 PEARLESCENT then  should
be constructed as follows:

PearlescentMaterial material = new PearlescentMaterial("PEARLESCENT");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 RUBBER then  should
be constructed as follows:

RubberMaterial material = new RubberMaterial("RUBBER");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 MATTE_METALLIC then  should
be constructed as follows:

MatteMetallicMaterial material = new MatteMetallicMaterial("MATTE_METALLIC");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 METAL then  should
be constructed as follows:

MetalMaterial material = new MetalMaterial("METAL");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 MATERIAL GLITTER VALUE #123456 FRACTION 0.5 VFRACTION 0.5 SIZE 3 then
 should be constructed as follows:

GlitterMaterial material = new GlitterMaterial("MATERIAL GLITTER VALUE #123456 FRACTION 0.5 VFRACTION 0.5 SIZE 3");

If the !COLOUR meta-command is !COLOUR name CODE 0 VALUE #123456 EDGE 1 MATERIAL SPECKLE VALUE #123456 FRACTION 0.5 SIZE 3 then
 should be constructed as follows:

SpeckleMaterial material = new SpeckleMaterial("MATERIAL GLITTER VALUE #123456 FRACTION 0.5 SIZE 3");

